-- Puma to Restate 2009 Earnings Over `Irregularities' at Greek Joint Venture
-- B y   M i k e   G a v i n
-- 2010-10-25T06:53:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/puma-to-restate-2009-earnings-over-irregularities-at-greek-joint-venture.html
Puma AG said “irregularities”
committed by a Greek joint venture partner will affect its
financial statements. Puma will have to restate statements, and
said its maximum extraordinary write-off effect “should not
execeed pretax 115 million euros.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
